^[^']*$
Here is the breakdown of the regex:
^ - asserts the start of the string
[^']* - matches any character that is not a single quotation mark ('), zero or more times
$ - asserts the end of the string

^(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\d)(?=.*[!@#$%^&*])[a-zA-Z\d!@#$%^&*]{min,max}$
Note: Replace "min" and "max" with the desired minimum and maximum lengths for the password.
